<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Chicken Scratch on MarkJacobsen.net</title><link>https://markjacobsen.net/categories/chicken-scratch/</link><description>Recent content in Chicken Scratch on MarkJacobsen.net</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Mon, 15 Nov 2021 23:29:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://markjacobsen.net/categories/chicken-scratch/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Labeling != Pigeonholing</title><link>https://markjacobsen.net/2021/11/labeling-is-not-pigeonholing/</link><pubDate>Mon, 15 Nov 2021 23:29:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://markjacobsen.net/2021/11/labeling-is-not-pigeonholing/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;I find it interesting how we’ve made “labeling” into a negative. At least it feels that way to me. But labels are one of the most convenient and flexible ways of categorizing things (including people) that there is.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Just a few labels you can feel free to apply to me: developer, realtor, father, athlete, introvert, extrovert, kind, jerk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;…and I’m sure there are plenty of others (even negative or conflicting ones like some of the above) you could apply to me. Season for taste… your taste.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Either way, if I “label” you, it’s not a negative. Maybe you could consider the fact that I find you important enough to even take the time to “label”.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now, if I pigeonhole you then you might care, but by that point it probably doesn’t to you.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Chicken Scratch: 2017-10-11</title><link>https://markjacobsen.net/2017/10/chicken-scratch-2017-10-11/</link><pubDate>Wed, 11 Oct 2017 12:07:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://markjacobsen.net/2017/10/chicken-scratch-2017-10-11/</guid><description>&lt;img data-recalc-dims="1" loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://i0.wp.com/markjacobsen.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/img_1914.jpg?resize=474%2C278" height="278" class="wp-image-1431" width="474" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/markjacobsen.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/img_1914.jpg?w=2843&amp;ssl=1 2843w, https://i0.wp.com/markjacobsen.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/img_1914.jpg?resize=300%2C176&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/markjacobsen.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/img_1914.jpg?resize=768%2C451&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/markjacobsen.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/img_1914.jpg?resize=1024%2C602&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/markjacobsen.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/img_1914.jpg?w=948&amp;ssl=1 948w, https://i0.wp.com/markjacobsen.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/img_1914.jpg?w=1422&amp;ssl=1 1422w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 474px) 100vw, 474px" /&gt;</description></item><item><title>Chicken Scratch: 2017-10-05</title><link>https://markjacobsen.net/2017/10/chicken-scratch-2017-10-05/</link><pubDate>Fri, 06 Oct 2017 00:35:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://markjacobsen.net/2017/10/chicken-scratch-2017-10-05/</guid><description>&lt;img data-recalc-dims="1" loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://i0.wp.com/markjacobsen.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/img_1890.jpg?resize=474%2C329" height="329" class="wp-image-1426" width="474" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/markjacobsen.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/img_1890.jpg?w=3975&amp;ssl=1 3975w, https://i0.wp.com/markjacobsen.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/img_1890.jpg?resize=300%2C208&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/markjacob